Description: Be sure to blow up the pics to get a good look at everything, and read the description carefully. Thanks for looking! 2011 Fender Custom Shop Time Machine 1959 Esquire, in Candy Apple Red, modded with neck pickup and three way switch. The back of the neck was stripped and finished with oil. Everything else is stock. Top-loader bridge. See pics for dings, etc. This is not a relic model, so everything you see in the pics is from playwear. Very little fretwear. The mods were done by a previous owner, so I don't know what the neck pickup is, but the sound is extremely well-balanced with the bridge pickup. Includes original hard case, case candy, COA, etc, as shown in pics. More specs: Body Material: Ash Body Neck Material: Maple Neck Fingerboard Material: Rosewood Fingerboard Neck Profile: C Neck Thickness (IN): 1st fret: .86", 12th fret: .95" Fingerboard Radius: 7.25 Nut Width: 1-5/8 in Neck Details: One-piece maple neck with slab rosewood fingerboard and clay dot inlays. Back of neck has been stripped and finished with oil. Electronics: Neck pickup installed. All routes are original from the factory. Three-way switch with master volume and master tone. Pickup Measurements: Bridge: 7.0K, Neck: 7.1K Hardware: Pickguard has been replaced to accommodate neck pickup. Weight: 7 lbs 10 oz
Title: Fender Custom Shop 2011 left handed 1959 NOS Time Machine Esquire lefty CAR
